## Summary & Conclusions

**Question 1: Has China reached life expectancy comparable to developed countries?**

**Yes.** China's 2023 life expectancy of **77.9 years** exceeds both the World average (73.2) and the Upper-Middle-Income Countries benchmark (75.9). China's gain of 34+ years since 1950 is extraordinary — driven by healthcare investment, poverty reduction, and improved nutrition. China now sits firmly in the range associated with high-income, developed nations.

**Question 2: Which countries show fertility trends most similar to China?**

China's fertility rate of **0.999 children per woman (2023)** is among the world's lowest, reflecting decades of the one-child policy and rising urbanisation. The most similar countries are:

-   🇺🇦 **Ukraine** (0.977) — closest match
-   🇸🇬 **Singapore** (0.943)
-   🇵🇷 **Puerto Rico** (0.941)
-   🇹🇼 **Taiwan** (0.870)
-   🇰🇷 **South Korea** (0.720)

All share rapid economic development, high urbanisation, and shifting attitudes toward family formation.
